postcontent:
I bought this a few months ago. I took it home, cleaned it, fired 35 rounds through it, cleaned it again and haven't touched it since. The gun shoots the 5.7x28mm cartridge, a very capable cartridge that was designed by FN with the intent of penetrating soft body armor. The gun uses the standard Five-seveN magazines. The standard magazine holds 20 rounds, however, there are 30 rounders made and 10 round extensions to increase your magazine capacity to 30 rounds. The gun has a muzzle brake/compensator, non-reciprocating charging handle, and a picatinny rail on top for mounting a red dot or other optics. The gun utilizes the MAC design which means it is very reliable and built like a tank. It uses a straight blowback design which means that there is very little to go wrong. The gun is also very accurate (For what it is.) because of the low recoil nature of the round. The gun is also very fun to shoot. (I know from experience.)
